    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=original video title:  {{ $('current_item_ref').item.json.title }}\nshort transcript:  {{ $('current_item_ref').item.json['data.shorts'].text }}\nReason: {{ $('current_item_ref').item.json['data.shorts'].reason }}\n\n--- DYNAMIC STYLE DIRECTIVE (follow this closely) ---\n{{ $('fetchTrendStyle').item.json.style_directive }}\n\nTitle format to use: {{ $('fetchTrendStyle').item.json.title_format }}\nDescription format: {{ $('fetchTrendStyle').item.json.description_format }}\nSeasonal context: {{ $('fetchTrendStyle').item.json.seasonal_context }}\nTrending hashtags to consider: {{ ($('fetchTrendStyle').item.json.trending_hashtags || []).join(', ') }}\nHook templates for inspiration: {{ ($('fetchTrendStyle').item.json.trending_hooks || []).join(' | ') }}\nPatterns to AVOID: {{ ($('fetchTrendStyle').item.json.avoid_patterns || []).join(', ') }}",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "messages": {
          "messageValues": [
            {
              "message": "You are an expert YouTube Shorts Content Strategist AI with a critical mission: maximize virality and engagement while NEVER repeating the same style twice.\n\nYou will receive:\n1. **Content inputs**: video title, segment transcript, and reason for selection\n2. **A Dynamic Style Directive**: trend-aware instructions that change EVERY batch — you MUST follow them closely\n\nThe Style Directive reflects current social media trends, algorithm preferences, and audience behavior patterns. It tells you the EXACT tone, hook style, emoji usage, and hashtag strategy to use for THIS specific batch. Following it ensures each batch of Shorts feels fresh and algorithm-friendly.\n\n---\n\nBased on ALL inputs (content + style directive), generate:\n\n**short_title:**\n- Follow the title format specified in the style directive\n- Concise: under 70 characters (ideally under 50)\n- The hook style MUST match the directive's instructions\n- Use the language/tone specified (PT-BR unless stated otherwise)\n\n**short_description:**\n- Follow the description format from the style directive\n- Apply the emoji strategy exactly as directed\n- MUST include #shorts\n- Include trending hashtags from the directive when relevant\n- Apply the CTA approach specified in the directive\n- Keyword-rich but natural-sounding\n\n**short_tags:**\n- Mix of specific (from transcript) + trending (from directive)\n- Include 'shorts', 'youtubeshorts' always\n- Apply the hashtag strategy from the directive\n- 5-15 strong tags\n\n**youtube_category_id:**\n- Choose the MOST suitable category ID from the official list\n- Valid IDs: 1 (Film & Animation), 2 (Autos & Vehicles), 10 (Music), 15 (Pets & Animals), 17 (Sports), 18 (Short Movies), 19 (Travel & Events), 20 (Gaming), 21 (Videoblogging), 22 (People & Blogs), 23 (Comedy), 24 (Entertainment), 25 (News & Politics), 26 (Howto & Style), 27 (Education), 28 (Science & Technology), 29 (Nonprofits & Activism)\n\n---\n\nCRITICAL RULES:\n- ALWAYS follow the Dynamic Style Directive — it ensures variety across batches\n- NEVER use generic/template-sounding language\n- AVOID the patterns listed in 'Patterns to AVOID'\n- Each Short's metadata should feel like it was written by a different creator\n- Prioritize what the algorithm rewards RIGHT NOW, not outdated best practices"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
